5xFAD mouse analysis

1. Import Data

We will firstly import the counts data and sample metadata from GEO.

The counts were downloaded as the GSE140286_FAD_time_series_rnaseq_raw_count.txt.gz file from the GEO accession GSE140286.

The names of the samples are:

The samples were then retrieved from GEO and converted into a tibble.

samples <- getGEO(filename = here::here("R/Mouse/data/GSE140286_series_matrix.txt"), getGPL = FALSE) %>%
  phenoData %>%
  pData %>%
  as_tibble

There is a lot of metadata which will be not relevant to our analysis, so lets keep only the relevant columns corresponding to age in months, genotype, and tissue. The samples table now looks like this:

Check the id column in samples corresponds to the sampleNames.

samples$id %in% sampleNames

 [1] TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE

2. Analysis

Like our other DE analyses, we will format the data to do a limma-voom-based analysis.

In this analysis, we will perform the comparison mutant (5XFAD) vs WT to:

  • identify DE genes (might be able to see some overlap / concordance between this and our zebrafish dataset)
  • gene set enrichment analysis with Hallmark / KEGG gene sets
  • gene set enrichment analysis with IRE gene sets

2.1. DE gene analysis
